<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">architrave</rs> block, damaged along all edges, from which the cornice and part of the right side of the first fascia have been erased in adaptation for a secondary use (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">2.42</measure>   × <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.38</measure>   × <measure dim="depth" type="length" unit="metre">0.54</measure>)</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on each of the three fasciae.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>l.1, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.095</measure>; l.2, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.085</measure>; l.3, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.06</measure> (no letter complete).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0037" notAfter="0041" exact="both" cert="low">A.D. 37-41</date>
(<rs type="criteria">emperor</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="1"/><gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w>Δήμωι</w> <del status="unremarkable"><gap extent="12" reason="lost" unit="character"/></del><lb n="2"/><gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>  <persName type="divine" full="yes">Ὁμονοίας</persName> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><name reg="Γάϊος">Γαίου</name>  <name reg="Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρος</name></persName>  <space unit="character" extent="4" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="3"/><gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>  <space unit="character" extent="4" dim="horizontal"/>  <w lemma="καί"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">καὶ</supplied></w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὰ</w> <w lemma="ἐν">ἐν</w> <w>αὐτῶι</w> <w>ἀνέ<unclear reason="damage">θ</unclear>ηκ<unclear reason="damage">α</unclear>ν</w>      <space unit="character" extent="4" dim="horizontal"/></ab>
</div>
<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds).</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>. . .] and for the People [ . . .] of Homonoia and Gaius Caesar [ . . .] and the things )?decorations, statues) on it, they set up.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>l. 2 perhaps indicates a priest, but the genitives might just be explained as indicating the functions of the monument (<foreign lang="grc">τὸν νάον</foreign>, etc.)</p><p>Is Gaius Caesar Caligula?  [[[Check the association of his sister with Homonoia.]]]</p><p>There is no doubt that at Aphrodisias the reign of Caligula was of some significance in the development of the Imperial cult.</p><p>See <bibl>Reynolds, 'Ruler-cult', 43</bibl></p>
</div>
